<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-100] Core union operation does not sort result nodes according to document order</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-100</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Source document:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;MAIN&amp;gt;&amp;lt;A&amp;gt;avalue&amp;lt;/A&amp;gt;&amp;lt;B&amp;gt;bvalue&amp;lt;/B&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/MAIN&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to string() function defintion:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;A node-set is converted to a string by returning the string-value of the node in the node-set that is first in document order. If the node-set is empty, an empty string is returned.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following XPath calculated incorrectly:&lt;br/&gt;
 string(/MAIN/B | /MAIN/A)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected result: &quot;avalue&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Actual value: &quot;bvalue&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reason:&lt;br/&gt;
sorting of result nodes is missing from CoreOperationUnion&lt;/p&gt;</description>
